This is a regression introduced in this commit https://github.com/apache/incubator-openwhisk/commit/9be13e2c6d581f42b60351f05a11e4aa71ca31d9#diff-9399daa47aa3257bb6bcb49425f4389dR109.

FYI @dubeejw. The `WhiskEntityJsonFormat` violates the invariant that `WhiskEntityJsonFormat` formerly asserted (we had some test coverage here but not sufficient). I believe the latter is now deadcode as a result of the change in the noted commit.

The following test addition to `TriggersApiTests` will reproduce the bug.

```scala
 it should "report Conflict if the name was of a different type" in {
    implicit val tid = transid()
    val action = WhiskAction(namespace, aname(), jsDefault("??"))
    put(entityStore, action)
    Get(s"/$namespace/${collection.path}/${action.name}") ~> Route.seal(routes(creds)) ~> check {
      status should be(Conflict)
    }
  }
```
